# Architecture Rules

- Strict separation of concerns:
  - `weather.py`: ONLY API fetch/parse logic. No print statements, no advice logic.
  - `calendar_reader.py`: ONLY reads and validates calendar.json. No print statements.
  - `advisor.py`: ONLY rule-based reasoning combining weather + calendar data into advice. No I/O, no print statements, no API calls.
  - `cli.py`: ONLY the REPL loop, user input/output, and orchestration calls into the other modules. No business logic here.
- Every function should have a docstring and type hints.
- Do not mix UI (print/input) with logic modules. If a module needs to "say" something, it should return a string/object and let cli.py print it.
- Prefer pure functions in advisor.py so they are easy to unit test without mocking I/O.
- This project uses Windows PowerShell as the terminal. Any terminal commands suggested should use PowerShell syntax, not bash/Unix syntax.
- Advice synthesis is rule-based (see specs/PRD.md Section 4) — do not introduce LLM API calls for advice generation without explicit confirmation.